The paper deals with secure communication in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple antennas at the legitimate receivers and eavesdroppers is a common technique in wireless communication, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also deals with the problem of unknown eavesdroppers, which is a topic that falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and system and control (cs.SI).
